Opposition leaders on Monday held Lebanese and Syrian governments responsible for the assassination of former Prime Minister Rafik Hariri, demanded Syrian troops withdraw from Lebanon within the next three months and called on the international community to intervene to help "this captive nation."
Syrian President Bashar al-Assad  on Monday condemned a blast which killed former Lebanese Prime  Minister Rafik Hariri as "horrible terrorist act," the official  SANA news agency reported.
Lebanese President Emile Lahoud on  Thursday reappointed pro-Syrian Omar Karami to be the country's new premier, 10 days after Karami resigned under massive protests and  pressure.
